# Second line of defence — uploaded to the Laravel app root as `.htaccess`.
# If the docroot rewrite ever gets bypassed (e.g. mod_rewrite disabled, an
# admin panel toggling routing), this still denies every request hitting
# the application directory.
#
# Apache 2.4+ syntax. The deny rule is unconditional — no client should
# ever fetch files from this directory.

Require all denied

<FilesMatch ".*">
    Require all denied
</FilesMatch>
